One of 'em's the Bible,
one of 'em's a book on Christmas,

232
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:10,754
one of 'em's on how to be a carpenter.

233
00:23:10,822 --> 00:23:15,122
- Why do you carry them around with you?
- I ain't got no place to set 'em down.

234
00:23:15,193 --> 00:23:17,320
Don't you live somewhere?

235
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:20,263
Did live up there in the state hospital.

236
00:23:20,332 --> 00:23:24,428
- Why did you live there?
- I killed some folks quite a while back.

237
00:23:24,503 --> 00:23:27,939
They said I wasn't right in the head, so they
put me there in the nervous hospital

238
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:30,236
instead of putting me in jail.

239
00:23:30,308 --> 00:23:32,970
- They let you out?
- Yeah.

240
00:23:33,044 --> 00:23:36,810
- How come?
- They told me I was well.

241
00:23:36,882 --> 00:23:39,646
Had to turn me loose.

242
00:23:39,718 --> 00:23:43,654
- Well, are you well?
- I reckon I feel all right.

243
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:48,256
This here's my house.

244
00:23:50,962 --> 00:23:54,693
You don't seem like you'd kill nobody.

245
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:56,961
We can just set these bags on the porch.

246
00:23:57,035 --> 00:23:59,560
All right, then.

247
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:17,547
You like to play football?

248
00:24:17,622 --> 00:24:22,491
I never was no account at it.
I never did get picked out for it.

249
00:24:22,561 --> 00:24:24,961
Well, me and the Burnett twins
and some boys play

250
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:27,692
at the junior high school field all the time.

251
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:32,203
If you wanna play, you can come on over,
'cause we ain't no good either.

252
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:35,967
- Well, I'll see you later.
- All right, then.

253
00:25:29,661 --> 00:25:31,492
Karl.

254
00:25:31,563 --> 00:25:34,157
Hon, you can't just go in there.

255
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,298
Karl, what in the world are you doing here?

256
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:39,963
I wanna come back and stay in here.

257
00:25:40,972 --> 00:25:43,236
You can't do that.
You're a free man.

258
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:46,141
They let you out
so you can do as you please.

259
00:25:46,211 --> 00:25:48,873
I reckon I don't care nothing
about being a free man.

260
00:25:48,947 --> 00:25:51,507
I don't know how to go about it. Mm-hm.

261
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:55,747
Well, you're gonna have to learn.
It'll take some time.

262
00:25:55,820 --> 00:25:58,721
Don't you have anybody down there
to help you out?

263
00:25:58,790 --> 00:26:01,054
No, sir.

264
00:26:01,126 --> 00:26:06,325
Well, your daddy was living down there
the last time I heard.

265
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:10,391
I guess he wouldn't want
to help you out any, would he?

266
00:26:10,468 --> 00:26:12,800
Sorry, I wasn't thinking.

267
00:26:15,206 --> 00:26:17,504
Don't you have anybody?

268
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:19,669
No, sir.

269
00:26:19,744 --> 00:26:22,679
Never did know too much
of nobody down there.

270
00:26:22,747 --> 00:26:25,238
Not to be helping me out no way. Mm-hm.

271
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:32,652
Look, Karl, the truth is,
I don't know where they expect you to go,

272
00:26:32,724 --> 00:26:34,885
and I don't know
what they expect you to do.

273
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:39,659
If it was up to me, you could
come back here and stay if you wanted to.

274
00:26:39,731 --> 00:26:42,529
I'm just trying to do my job.

275
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:44,762
You follow me?

276
00:26:47,973 --> 00:26:54,037
Listen, Karl. I know an old boy
who's got a fix-it shop deal in Millsberg.

277
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:56,603
He used to go to church with me.

278
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,976
You're good working
on small engines and things.

279
00:27:01,052 --> 00:27:05,318
If I was to put my neck out for you with him,

280
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:09,326
do you think you could work it
if he'll hire you?

281
00:27:10,328 --> 00:27:14,355
I'm pretty handy, I reckon,
on lawn mowers and whatnot. Mm-hm.

282
00:27:14,432 --> 00:27:17,367
I know you are, I've seen it myself.

283
00:27:17,435 --> 00:27:20,427
- Could you give it a try?
- I reckon.

284
00:27:22,107 --> 00:27:25,907
Now, I...
I can't promise you that he'll hire you.

285
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:29,378
I'll have to tell him about your history.

286
00:27:29,447 --> 00:27:32,143
I never was no good with history. Mm-hm.

287
00:27:32,217 --> 00:27:35,186
No. I mean your past.

288
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:39,950
Why you were in here.

289
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:44,390
I'll take you down first thing in the morning.

290
00:27:45,397 --> 00:27:48,855
You don't have anywhere
you could stay tonight at all?

291
00:27:48,933 --> 00:27:50,696
- No, sir.
- Well, you can't stay here.

292
00:27:50,769 --> 00:27:56,298
It's against the rules.
If something was to happen, I'd be liable.

293
00:27:58,043 --> 00:28:00,477
I reckon I can just walk around
till morning time.

294
00:28:00,545 --> 00:28:03,343
And sit and read a book somewheres.
Mm-hm.

295
00:28:21,232 --> 00:28:24,030
Karl, would you like a muffin?

296
00:28:24,102 --> 00:28:26,093
No, thank you.

297
00:28:29,841 --> 00:28:34,608
I understand Jerry's gonna take you
someplace else tomorrow.

298
00:28:34,679 --> 00:28:38,240
I don't reckon I know nobody named Jerry.

299
00:28:38,316 --> 00:28:42,047
She's talking about me, Karl.
That's my first name.

300
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:46,750
He's carrying me to look for work down
in Millsberg, where I was born. Mm-hm.

301
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:51,218
Would you like some coffee?

302
00:28:51,296 --> 00:28:55,460
Coffee makes me a mite nervous
when I drink it.

303
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,594
Daddy, can I be excused to go to bed?

304
00:28:58,670 --> 00:29:01,104
Sure, honey.
You sleep with your momma tonight.

305
00:29:01,172 --> 00:29:04,039
I'm gonna sleep with your brother,
so Karl can have your room.

306
00:29:04,109 --> 00:29:05,633
Why?

307
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:09,103
'Cause he's company.

308
00:29:20,358 --> 00:29:23,885
Well, Karl, looks like you got
plenty of blankets and things.

309
00:29:23,962 --> 00:29:27,022
Bathroom's out there in the hall.

310
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:29,225
We'll leave at first light.

311
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:32,599
That's a... that's an old cowboy thing.

312
00:29:57,162 --> 00:30:00,689
Jerry, why didn't you give him Bubba's
room? His sister's is a little girly, isn't it?

313
00:30:00,765 --> 00:30:04,257
Yeah, I thought about that. I guess it
doesn't make any sense to move him now.

314
00:30:04,335 --> 00:30:06,030
Daddy...

315
00:30:06,104 --> 00:30:11,269
Don't you think one of us ought to stay up
all night and kind of guard or something?

316
00:30:11,342 --> 00:30:13,776
Well, hell, no, son.
What's wrong with you?

317
00:30:13,845 --> 00:30:18,680
- He's a nut, ain't he?
- "Isn't," Bubba. Don't say "ain't."

318
00:30:30,528 --> 00:30:31,790
("Knocks at door)

319
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:35,162
- Karl, are you up?
- Yes, sir.

320
00:30:39,037 --> 00:30:41,130
Didn't you go to sleep at all, Karl?

321
00:30:41,206 --> 00:30:43,299
You been sitting there like that all night?

322
00:30:43,374 --> 00:30:45,467
Yes, sir.

323
00:30:45,543 --> 00:30:48,637
Well, come on.
We'd better hit the road.

324
00:30:48,713 --> 00:30:51,079
All right, then.

325
00:31:43,801 --> 00:31:46,395
- Hey, Jerry. How's it going?
- Hey, Bill.

326
00:31:46,471 --> 00:31:48,166
Good to see you, man.
It's been a long time.

327
00:31:48,239 --> 00:31:50,434
It's good to see you, too.
How's everybody doing?

328
00:31:50,508 --> 00:31:54,569
Oh, pretty good. Kids are driving me crazy,
Phyllis is gonna put me in the poorhouse,

329
00:31:54,646 --> 00:31:58,343
but I can't complain other than that.
Wouldn't do any good if I did.

330
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:00,782
- You know Scooter, Jerry?
- I don't believe I do.

331
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:03,980
- Good to meet you, Scooter.
- How about you?

332
00:32:04,055 --> 00:32:06,546
Well, this is him, the one
I was telling you about on the phone.

333
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:09,593
Like I said, if you get nervous about it,
I'll understand.

334
00:32:09,661 --> 00:32:13,188
I'm not gonna lie to you. He did get
into that trouble, but then he was young.

335
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:17,200
I remember that real well. He cut those
folks to pieces, his momma was one of 'em.

336
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:19,168
Yeah, and that old Dixon boy.

337
00:32:19,237 --> 00:32:23,367
Oh, hell, I always wanted to kill him myself.
Asshole's what he was.

338
00:32:23,441 --> 00:32:28,640
I remember that old boy, too. Kind of
retarded or something back in school.

339
00:32:28,713 --> 00:32:32,774
Well, seems like he's
pretty well-adjusted these days.

340
00:32:32,850 --> 00:32:35,751
He... I don't think he'd ever hurt anybody.

341
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:37,845
He don't look much like he would.

342
00:32:37,922 --> 00:32:40,447
You say he fixes small engines
like nobody's business?

343
00:32:40,525 --> 00:32:43,187
He's a regular whiz.
It's all he's done since he was a kid.

344
00:32:43,261 --> 00:32:47,493
- Are you scared of him, Scooter?
- No, I don't guess so.

345
00:32:47,565 --> 00:32:49,624
- Can he talk?
- Oh, yeah.

346
00:32:49,701 --> 00:32:52,431
Now, you say he can stay out the back?

347
00:32:52,503 --> 00:32:56,564
Fine with me. If he steals anything, I'm
gonna take it out of your pocket anyway.

348
00:32:56,641 --> 00:33:00,133
Oh, he won't steal. He's a pretty good
old boy, really. Keeps to himself.

349
00:33:00,211 --> 00:33:04,875
Well, I got a roomful of work for him to do.
I can't get Scooter to do any of it.

350
00:33:04,949 --> 00:33:09,181
Karl, come over here.
I want you to meet your new boss.

351
00:33:09,253 --> 00:33:11,278
This is Bill Cox.

352
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:14,917
He runs the place. Says that you
can work here and stay out back.

353
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:18,520
- It's good to know you, Karl.
- Thank you.

354
00:33:18,596 --> 00:33:20,791
Karl, it's minimum wage,
and there ain't nothing back there

355
00:33:20,865 --> 00:33:23,265
but an old army cot and a toilet.

356
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:26,895
Yeah, that'll be fine. Karl, I'm gonna
go out to the car and get your books.

357
00:33:26,971 --> 00:33:28,962
All right, then.

358
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:36,271
Karl, they say you're a whiz
on fixing lawn mowers and things.

359
00:33:36,347 --> 00:33:39,578
I've tinkered around on 'em a little bit.
Mm-hm.

360
00:33:40,585 --> 00:33:43,452
We order up from the Frostee Cream
at lunch, usually.

361
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:47,218
We can buy you lunch
till you get on your feet a little.

362
00:33:47,291 --> 00:33:50,624
I like them French-fried potatoes. Mm-hm.

363
00:33:51,596 --> 00:33:53,587
Yeah? Me, too.

364
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:58,892
They make a good double meat burger.

365
00:34:11,916 --> 00:34:14,282
All right, then.
I'll see y'all later.

366
00:34:14,352 --> 00:34:17,753
Karl, you done a good day's work today.
They was right about you.

367
00:34:17,822 --> 00:34:21,280
Scooter, he gonna knock you out of a job
if you're not careful.

368
00:34:21,359 --> 00:34:27,355
- All right, then, I'll see y'all tomorrow.
- Wait up. I'll leave with you and lock up.

369
00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:29,127
Karl, there's a blanket up in under that cot

370
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:32,192
and some soap in the bathroom
for cleaning up with.

371
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:36,263
Now, there's one more thing. The way we
lock these doors, you can't get out at night.

372
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:40,003
- You didn't wanna go anywhere, did you?
- I don't reckon.

373
00:34:40,078 --> 00:34:43,878
If it works out, maybe we'll get you a key
so you can get out at night if you need to.

374
00:34:43,948 --> 00:34:47,145
- I'll see you later.
- All right, then.

375
00:34:59,163 --> 00:35:04,362
So then the old man says, "At my age,
I'd rather have the talking frog."

376
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:06,596
We'll see you, JW.

377
00:35:25,990 --> 00:35:29,619
Scooter, did I tell you the one about
the two old boys pissing off the bridge?

378
00:35:29,694 --> 00:35:32,891
- I don't remember.
- Well...

379
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:36,263
These two old boys hung their peckers
off the bridge to piss.

380
00:35:36,334 --> 00:35:39,633
And one of the boys was from California
and one from Arkansas.

381
00:35:39,704 --> 00:35:42,935
Old boy from California says,
"Boy, this water's cold."

382
00:35:43,007 --> 00:35:47,637
Old boy from Arkansas said,
"Yeah, and it's deep, too."

383
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:51,738
Get it?

384
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:54,512
- That's a good 'un.
- That is a good one.

385
00:35:54,585 --> 00:35:56,985
You know, I do believe
you've told me that one before.

386
00:35:57,054 --> 00:35:59,079
I've heard that one a bunch.

387
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:03,287
- A long time ago.
- Yeah, that's a classic.

388
00:36:03,361 --> 00:36:05,591
You know, Karl,
I got to thinking about it last night,

389
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:08,826
and it's just not Christian of me
not to let you have a key.

390
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:11,630
I mean, you've been in lockup so long,
you don't need me keeping you locked up.

391
00:36:11,702 --> 00:36:13,863
You need to come and go as you please.

392
00:36:13,938 --> 00:36:15,769
Here.

393
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:20,368
Take this key.
It'll get you in and out of here at night.

394
00:36:21,679 --> 00:36:23,670
All right, then.

395
00:36:25,883 --> 00:36:30,286
- Them French fries good?
- Yeah, they're good all right. Mm-hm.

396
00:36:31,455 --> 00:36:33,548
You got any money?

397
00:36:34,559 --> 00:36:38,825
Well, they give me some
when they turned me loose.

398
00:36:38,896 --> 00:36:44,630
I spent up some of it a-ridin' on the bus
and eating French-fried potatoes. Mm-hm.

399
00:36:44,702 --> 00:36:48,297
Well, I'm gonna pay you today
for this coming week

400
00:36:48,372 --> 00:36:50,772
so you have some walking-around money.

401
00:36:50,841 --> 00:36:53,241
When you get off this evening,
you need to go buy some toothpaste

402
00:36:53,311 --> 00:36:56,041
and some cleaning up supplies
to have back there.

403
00:36:56,113 --> 00:36:59,514
Get you some magazines
and some hard candy.

404
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:02,109
Something to keep you busy at night.

405
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:05,111
All right, then.

406
00:37:05,189 --> 00:37:08,784
I'll let you off while it's still daylight.

407
00:37:40,057 --> 00:37:43,458
Hey, there.
I thought I heard somebody on the porch.

408
00:37:43,527 --> 00:37:46,155
Wasn't your name Karl?

409
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:49,563
Yes, sir, it is.
Your name's Frank.

410
00:37:50,334 --> 00:37:53,633
Yeah. What are you doing by here?

411
00:37:53,704 --> 00:37:56,036
You said for me to come by.

412
00:37:56,107 --> 00:37:58,268
You wanna play ball with us?

413
00:37:58,342 --> 00:38:02,574
I ain't no good at it.
I just come by to see you. Mm-hm.

414
00:38:02,647 --> 00:38:05,810
Well, I was going to see my momma
over at Hoochy's Dollar Store.

415
00:38:05,883 --> 00:38:08,078
She works two till eight.

416
00:38:08,152 --> 00:38:10,814
All right, then.

417
00:38:10,888 --> 00:38:14,380
You wanna go with me?
You can meet my momma.

418
00:38:15,626 --> 00:38:18,060
I oughta not worry your momma
with company.

419
00:38:18,129 --> 00:38:22,156
Aw, come on. You'll like her.
She's real nice.

420
00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:26,033
And she'll give us anything we want her to.
Candy or something.

421
00:38:27,805 --> 00:38:30,774
Well, I was kindly needing
to do some trading.

422
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:32,934
Reckon they sell toothpaste?

423
00:38:33,010 --> 00:38:36,309
Yeah, they sell a little bit of everything.

424
00:38:36,380 --> 00:38:40,578
I won't tell her about you
being in the state hospital for killing.

425
00:38:40,651 --> 00:38:43,176
Come on, let's go.

426
00:38:57,435 --> 00:39:00,495
You're just gonna have to learn to live
without all that grease.

427
00:39:00,571 --> 00:39:02,596
Shoot, not here in the South.

428
00:39:02,673 --> 00:39:06,473
I like grease on everything.
I like fried chicken, fried okra.

429
00:39:06,544 --> 00:39:08,136
- Biscuits and gravy.
- It'll kill you.

430
00:39:08,212 --> 00:39:10,942
- Hey, Momma. Hey, Vaughan.
- Hey, sweetheart. What you up to?

431
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:13,779
I bet I know. You want
a whole bunch of candy and a pop, right?

432
00:39:13,851 --> 00:39:14,340
Yeah.

433
00:39:14,418 --> 00:39:18,184
That stuffs gonna rot your teeth, don't you
know that? I got something even better.

434
00:39:18,255 --> 00:39:21,816
I just put potted meat on special-four cans
for a dollar. They're not moving very well.

435
00:39:21,892 --> 00:39:26,158
But I tell you what, I'll give
a couple of cans for free to the right kid.

436
00:39:26,230 --> 00:39:28,221
I don't like potted meat.

437
00:39:28,299 --> 00:39:31,200
Daddy used to say they was made
out of lips, peckers and intest...

438
00:39:31,268 --> 00:39:33,259
Frank, don't talk that way.

439
00:39:33,337 --> 00:39:38,104
Who's that strange-looking man
behind you? Did he follow you in here?

440
00:39:38,175 --> 00:39:41,201
- Can I help you, sir?
- ("Frank) Oh, that's Karl.

441
00:39:41,278 --> 00:39:43,371
I met him at the Laundromat.

442
00:39:43,447 --> 00:39:48,441
Karl, this is Momma and Vaughan.
Vaughan's the manager.

443
00:39:48,519 --> 00:39:53,115
He lets Momma off any time
she feels like it, 'cause they're best friends.

444
00:39:53,190 --> 00:39:56,057
Nice to meet you, Karl.

445
00:39:56,127 --> 00:39:58,459
Pleased to meet you.

446
00:40:01,465 --> 00:40:05,799
Frank, why don't you
come back here with me for a minute?

447
00:40:10,574 --> 00:40:14,032
I don't think I've seen you here before.

448
00:40:14,111 --> 00:40:18,047
No, sir, I don't reckon you have. I don't
believe I've ever been in here before.

449
00:40:18,115 --> 00:40:21,573
I don't believe this store used to be here.

450
00:40:21,652 --> 00:40:26,089
It's been here 17 years.
You live here before, or something?

451
00:40:26,157 --> 00:40:30,253
I was born and raised here
up till I was 12 year old.

452
00:40:30,327 --> 00:40:32,557
What brings you back?

453
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:34,723
What's that you say?

454
00:40:35,733 --> 00:40:37,792
Why are you here now?

455
00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:41,670
They turned me loose
from the state hospital. Mm-hm.

456
00:40:41,739 --> 00:40:44,230
